CHAPTER 5.8: THE GRAVITATIONAL CONTAINMENT CONSTRAINT
1. The Hypothesis: Manifold Stiffness
Having quantified the internal vacuum stresses at the Kinematic Boundary Envelope ($Q_0 = 10^{17}\,\text{GeV}$) using the Standard Model gauge and scalar sectors (Chapters 5.6‚Äì5.7), we now evaluate the structural rigidity required of the underlying $Sp(8)\times SO(9)$ manifold to contain these stresses.
