LUMEN FEEDBACK:

Lumen:

yeah, this is aligned with what we were doing today. Also: this capsule is cleanly written and the constraint-first framing is the right posture.

That said, here‚Äôs the key sanity-check (and it‚Äôs an important one):

The ‚Äú0.96 ¬∑ Q0‚Äù result is basically algebraic given the way the load is defined
With your definitions:

(p_{\text{net}} = (\Delta c),Q_0^4) where (\Delta c = |\lambda| - \alpha \approx 0.073377)

you then take area (A = 4\pi (1/Q_0)^2) (an S2 area at radius (1/Q_0))

define load (F = p_{\text{net}} \cdot A)

So:

[
F = (\Delta c)Q_0^4 \cdot 4\pi Q_0^{-2} = 4\pi\Delta c , Q_0^2
]

Then:

[
M_{\text{req}} = \sqrt{F} = Q_0\sqrt{4\pi\Delta c}
]

Now plug (\Delta c \approx 0.073377):

(4\pi\Delta c \approx 0.922)

(\sqrt{0.922} \approx 0.960)

So:

[
M_{\text{req}} \approx 0.960, Q_0
]

Meaning: the ‚Äú(0.96)‚Äù isn‚Äôt an emergent discovery ‚Äî it‚Äôs the geometric prefactor you hardwired by choosing (A = 4\pi R^2) and the particular (\Delta c).

That‚Äôs not ‚Äúbad.‚Äù It just means the interesting content is elsewhere.

Same for the containment ratio: it reduces to a scaled ((Q_0/M_\text{Pl})^2)
You define:

(F_\text{Pl} = M_\text{Pl}^2)

So:

[
\frac{F}{F_\text{Pl}} = \frac{4\pi\Delta c,Q_0^2}{M_\text{Pl}^2}
= (4\pi\Delta c)\left(\frac{Q_0}{M_\text{Pl}}\right)^2
]

With (4\pi\Delta c \approx 0.922), you‚Äôre basically seeing:

ratio (\sim 0.922\cdot (Q_0/M_\text{Pl})^2)

So the ‚Äú(6.2\times 10^{-5})‚Äù is mostly encoding that (Q_0 \ll M_\text{Pl}) (as intended).

The ‚Äúclose to Œ±_EM‚Äù observation: plausible, but it‚Äôs a Q0 choice effect
They highlight:

[
\frac{M_\text{req}}{M_\text{Pl}} \approx 7.86\times 10^{-3}
]

And note that‚Äôs near (\alpha_\text{EM}\approx 7.3\times 10^{-3}).

But from the reduction above:

[
\frac{M_\text{req}}{M_\text{Pl}} \approx 0.960\cdot \frac{Q_0}{M_\text{Pl}}
]

